This felt really good. I spent a bunch of hours on this painting 7 or 8 years ago and simply didn’t care about it anymore. Why not give it the chance to become something new? Truthfully, part of what pushed me towards teaching was a general dwindling of interest in the work I was making throughout my 20’s. It served its purpose, but I got bored…I felt like I exorcised a lot of those demons and needed to make space for something new. Not totally sure yet what that will mean when it comes to painting, but I’ve learned a lot about the power of experimentation thanks to kiddos, so I’m happy to hang out in that space for a while. #wip #repurpose #newartdirection #experiment #ambiguity

About a year ago, my dude @ramirostudios and I created a little company so we could extend our collaborative practice of working with kids. Now Super-Stories is officially a non profit! We’ve done over 20 projects in the past year, ranging from school murals designed by students to DIY skate ramp building workshops. Please give us a follow @_superstories_ to see what we are up to 🤘🤘🤘
.
.
We were also stoked to chat with Victoria Fry for the @visionaryartcollective podcast about this adventure. The episode is available on iTunes, Spotify, and anywhere podcast episodes are streamed.
.

Experimenting with messiness, using materials that don’t allow much control. (tempera sticks and oil pastels) I’ve been thinking about control a lot over the past year and how little we have. 
.
I shifted towards teaching when I realized how bored I was with my own work and methods. It’s taught me to give up what I thought I was supposed to be making and get back into process for the sake of process. Trying to figure out how all this thinking will find its way back into my 2-D work. 😑

Almost there 🥹

Little pulp creature in progress - One of the cooler things I’ve done this summer is figure out how to make my own paper pulp sculpting material out of all the scrap and half-used paper I have hanging around thanks to kids’ projects. Painting O+ festival (@opositivefest) in Kingston! This is a @_superstories_ project and I am working with the students of JFK Elementary to cover some walls with student artwork. We are doing two sections, one with artwork from the JFK fourth graders and one with artwork by the super young kiddos from Head Start in Ellenville, Saugerties, and Plattekill, NY. This is my first Super-Stories Project and mural since becoming a parent and I am equal parts stoked and nervous 🤘
.
.
Thank you to @opositivefest and to @communityactionca for having us, and to the hardworking students and teachers who helped make this happen🤘
